<nav class="anchor-nav" aria-label="Journal sections"><div class="container"><a href="#essays">Essays</a><a href="#research">Research Notes</a><a href="#field-reports">Field Reports</a><a href="#fellow-stories">Fellow Stories</a><a href="#briefings">Briefings</a><a href="#impact">Impact</a></div></nav>
<section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">The US Fellows Journal</span><h2>A record of serious public-interest work</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>The Journal publishes essays, research notes, field reports, institutional briefings, Fellow stories, annual letters, and public-benefit research connected to the Society’s missions.</p></div><div class="grid grid--3">
<article class="journal-card" id="essays"><div class="journal-card__top"></div><div class="journal-card__body"><span class="journal-card__meta">Essays</span><h3>Ideas of public consequence</h3><p>Long-form reflection on service, institutions, science, dignity, civic life, and national purpose.</p></div></article><article class="journal-card" id="research"><div class="journal-card__top"></div><div class="journal-card__body"><span class="journal-card__meta">Research Notes</span><h3>Inquiry made useful</h3><p>Concise findings, methods, and questions arising from mission-aligned research.</p></div></article><article class="journal-card" id="field-reports"><div class="journal-card__top"></div><div class="journal-card__body"><span class="journal-card__meta">Field Reports</span><h3>Lessons from practice</h3><p>Observations from fellowship appointments, host institutions, and public-benefit projects.</p></div></article><article class="journal-card" id="fellow-stories"><div class="journal-card__top"></div><div class="journal-card__body"><span class="journal-card__meta">Fellow Stories</span><h3>People who choose to serve</h3><p>Profiles of talent, character, affiliation, and contribution across disciplines.</p></div></article><article class="journal-card" id="briefings"><div class="journal-card__top"></div><div class="journal-card__body"><span class="journal-card__meta">Institutional Briefings</span><h3>Knowledge for decision-makers</h3><p>Focused analysis for hosts, partners, advisors, and civic institutions.</p></div></article><article class="journal-card" id="impact"><div class="journal-card__top"></div><div class="journal-card__body"><span class="journal-card__meta">Impact & Annual Letters</span><h3>Accountability to mission</h3><p>Reports on service, contribution, institutional strength, and public benefit.</p></div></article>
  </div></div></section>
<section class="section section--navy"><div class="container"><div class="grid grid--2"><div><span class="eyebrow">Editorial Standard</span><h2>Clarity, rigor, and public usefulness</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Journal contributions should sharpen understanding, document credible experience, respect affected communities, and make knowledge more useful to institutions and the public.</p></div><div><ul class="check-list"><li>Connected to a Society mission</li><li>Grounded in evidence or clearly identified experience</li><li>Written for thoughtful public use</li><li>Respectful of confidentiality and institutional trust</li><li>Transparent about perspective and limitations</li></ul></div></div></div></section>
<section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="cta"><div><h2>Contribute to the public conversation.</h2><p>Fellows, advisors, hosts, and mission partners may express interest in contributing to the Journal.</p></div><div class="actions"><a class="button button--gold" href="institutional-briefings.html">Explore Briefings</a><a class="button button--outline" href="become-a-fellow.html">Become a Fellow</a></div></div></div></section>
<section class="section section--mist"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">What belongs in the Journal</span><h2>Different forms for different kinds of knowledge</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>The Journal distinguishes argument, research, direct experience, institutional synthesis, and impact reporting so readers can understand the basis and intended use of each contribution.</p></div><div class="grid grid--3"><article class="card"><h3>Ideas and inquiry</h3><p>Essays and research notes develop arguments, questions, methods, or emerging findings while making evidence and uncertainty visible.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>Knowledge from practice</h3><p>Field reports and Fellow stories document context, decisions, collaboration, limits, and lessons without turning one experience into a universal claim.</p></article><article class="card"><h3>Knowledge for institutions</h3><p>Briefings and impact reports organize evidence around a decision, operating question, contribution, or need for accountable learning.</p></article></div></div></section>
<section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="grid grid--2"><div><span class="eyebrow">Editorial review</span><h2>Trust is built before publication</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>Review considers whether a piece has a clear purpose, a sound basis, appropriate permissions, fair treatment of affected people, and language proportionate to what the author can actually support.</p></div><div><ul class="check-list"><li>Claims are distinguishable from interpretation and recommendation</li><li>Sources, methods, and material limitations are visible</li><li>Confidential or sensitive details are handled responsibly</li><li>Institutional and community contributions are represented fairly</li><li>The finished work offers readers a useful next question or practice</li></ul></div></div></div></section>
<section class="section section--blue"><div class="container"><div class="section-intro"><span class="eyebrow">A public record that compounds</span><h2>Publication is part of service</h2><div class="rule"></div><p>The Journal gives the Society a place to preserve hard-won learning across appointments and missions. Its purpose is not to manufacture activity or prestige, but to make credible knowledge available to people who can question it, adapt it, and carry it into further work.</p></div></div></section>
